data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span` of native-sized integers.** Both `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>` work with `stackalloc`:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[4];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint`/`nuint` are 8 bytes each. The feature has been available since C# 9 / .NET 5, when `nint` and `nuint` were introduced as first-class unmanaged types (which is the requirement for `stackalloc`).
